  "notes": [
    "The Electrical Engineering B.S. program is accredited by the Engineering Accreditation Commission of ABET, http://www.abet.org . The following transfer screening policy takes effect in fall 2024 and will be mandatory for all transfer students entering UC Santa Cruz fall 2026 and later. Transfer students entering UCSC prior to fall 2026 are encouraged to complete these requirements, but will still be considered for admission if they fulfill the 2023-2024 admissions screening requirements. Transfer Admission Screening Policy To be considered for admission to the Electrical Engineering B.S. major, transfer students must complete the following courses or their equivalents by the end of spring term for students planning to enter in the fall, with a C (2.0) or better in each course and an overall GPA of 2.80 in the courses: All of the following: MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics CSE 12: Computer Systems and Assembly Language and Lab (strongly recommended, required effective the fall 2026 admissions cycle) One of the following: AM 10: Mathematical Methods for Engineers I OR MATH 21: Linear Algebra One of the following: AM 20: Mathematical Methods for Engineers II OR MATH 24: Ordinary Differential Equations A year of calculus-based physics courses accepted as equivalent to: PHYS 5A: Introduction to Physics I AND PHYS 5L: Introduction to Physics I Laboratory PHYS 5B: Introduction to Physics II AND PHYS 5M: Introduction to Physics II Laboratory PHYS 5C: Introduction to Physics III AND PHYS 5N: Introduction to Physics III Laboratory In addition to the courses required for transfer, it is strongly recommended that students complete the following courses prior to transfer to ensure timely graduation: CSE 12: Computer Systems and Assembly Language and Lab ( required effective the fall 2026 admissions cycle) MATH 23A: Vector Calculus MATH 23B: Vector Calculus PHYS 5D: Introduction to Physics IV﻿ ECE 101: Introduction to Electronic Circuits ECE 101L: Introduction to Electronic Circuits Laboratory Prospective students are encouraged to prioritize required and recommended major preparation prior to transfer, and may additionally complete courses that articulate to UC Santa Cruz general education requirements as time allows. Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this major.",
    "All transfer applicants must satisfy University of California admissions eligibility requirements and campus admission selection criteria. All admission requirements must be completed by the end of spring prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility requirements and admission to UC Santa Cruz, please visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that ensures your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require the completion of specific preparatory courses and/or minimum GPA requirements. For detailed information about the screening requirements for this major, please refer to \"Transfer Admission Screening Policy\" below. Additional preparatory coursework listed in the “Recommended Preparation” section are not required for admission, but are strongly recommended. Completion of these courses will help ensure timely progress toward degree completion. More information and a list of screening majors and non-screening majors may be found on the Admissions website.",
    "The UC Santa Cruz Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate (IB), and A-Level examination credit policies may be found in the UC Santa Cruz General Catalog . AP, IBH, and A-level exams may or may not satisfy course requirements, depending on the specific exam."
